                <h1>Using <code>scanf()</code> for Input</h1>
        <p>The <code>scanf()</code> function is used to read input from the standard input stream (usually the keyboard) in C.</p>
        <p>Its basic syntax is:</p>
        <pre><code>scanf("format specifier", &amp;variable);</code></pre>
        <p>Here's a breakdown of the components:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Format Specifier:</strong> Specifies the type of data to be read.</li>
            <li><strong>&amp;variable:</strong> Address of the variable where the input will be stored.</li>
        </ul>
        
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="slide ">
