                <h1>Using <code>printf()</code> for Output</h1>
        <p>The <code>printf()</code> function is used to display output in C.</p>
        <p>Its basic syntax is:</p>
        <pre><code>printf("format string", value1, value2, ...);</code></pre>
        <p>The format string contains placeholders for the values to be printed.</p>
        <p>Here are some examples:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Printing an integer:</li>
            <pre><code>int num = 10;
printf("The number is: %d\n", num);</code></pre>
            <li>Printing a floating-point number:</li>
            <pre><code>float price = 25.99;
printf("The price is: %.2f\n", price);</code></pre>
           
